<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2006-05-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Human Bocavirus Infection, Canada</TITLE><BODY>Human Bocavirus was detected in 18 (1.5%) of 1,209 respiratory specimens collected in 2003 and 2004 in Canada. The main symptoms of affected patients were cough (78%), fever (67%), and sore throat (44%). Nine patients were hospitalized; of these, 8 (89%) were <5 years of age.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>